folder: Jamaica Avenue & Highland Place, Brooklyn, NY
text:
(1)
Jamaica Ave., south side, west of Highland Place, showing from left to right the homes of John Eldert (1873) and A.H.W. Van Sicklen (1873).  Both houses were demolished in 1925; the first to make way Force Tube Ave; and the second, to make way for a Y.M.C.A.  The first house if standing, would be at the S.W. corner of Highland Place and Jamaica Ave; the second, at the S.E. corner of Shepherd and Jamaica Aves.

April 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2)
The same, showing a closeup of the A.H.W. Van Sicklen house.

April 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
